{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 388 "2.  Pascal's Triangle.  Recall the definition of Pascal's Tria
ngle.   Use Maple to construct the first 10 rows of Pascal's Triangle.
 (The trick will be to get the coefficients to occur in the correct or
der.  The Maple command for generating a sequence might be helpful. It
 is   seq(expression(i),i=m..n);   where expression(i) is an expressio
n with index i and m..n is a range of numbers." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 3 "   " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 18 "for p fro
m 0 to 10" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 44 " do seq(coeff(expand((
a+1)^p),a,k), k=0..p);" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 3 "od;" }}
